    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="382" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Dupuy de Lôme</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Falmouth</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 24,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: In accordance with your
                            suggestion, our minister at Madrid will be cabled this afternoon to make
                            formal acceptance of the offer by Spain to settle the Mora claim on the
                            terms of a memorandum executed by yourself, myself, and the agent and
                            counsel for the private parties interested.</p>
                <p>Very truly, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
